It&#8217;s believed the principal at a primary school near Mossel Bay hit a nine-year-old boy with a plank. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Education Department says it s investigating an alleged corporal punishment incident at a Southern Cape school. It s believed the principal at Herbertsdale Primary School near Mossel Bay hit a nine-year-old boy with a plank. According to reports, the principal also threatened to expel the boy and other learners if they spoke out about the matter.Provincial Education Department spokesperson Millicent Merton says the incident was reported to the department on Wednesday. Corporal punishment is illegal in terms of the South African Shools Act. The Western Cape Education Department views incidents of corporal punishment in a serious light and fully investigates all allegations reported to the department. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)